If you, as a leader, as an initiator of the meeting, are not interested in solving the problem,

01:41:36.000 --> 01:41:37.000
it is better not to conduct a meeting.

01:41:38.000 --> 01:41:41.000
Otherwise, you will only waste your time and your subordinates' time, and you will get very tired.

01:41:42.000 --> 01:41:45.000
So, a formal process, on the basis of which a meeting is built.

01:41:46.000 --> 01:41:49.000
The first option is a report.

01:41:50.000 --> 01:41:52.000
This form is familiar to almost everyone.

01:41:52.000 --> 01:41:57.000
One of the participants of the meeting tells in detail about the results of his work,

01:41:58.000 --> 01:42:02.000
or shares the information that he considers important on a particular issue.

01:42:03.000 --> 01:42:05.000
The second option is a discussion.

01:42:06.000 --> 01:42:11.000
Discussing the importance of the information that the participant has told,

01:42:12.000 --> 01:42:16.000
discussing the points that other participants of the meeting are interested in,

01:42:17.000 --> 01:42:20.000
which seem important to them to solve the general problem.

01:42:20.000 --> 01:42:23.000
And the next formal process is an analysis.

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:29.000
An analysis of the provided information and a search for solutions to the current problems.

01:42:30.000 --> 01:42:33.000
The type of communication between the participants of the meeting.

01:42:34.000 --> 01:42:38.000
As already mentioned above, there are two types of communication.

01:42:39.000 --> 01:42:43.000
Effective and ineffective.

01:42:44.000 --> 01:42:51.000
Effective communication allows your team to work in a coordinated manner

01:42:52.000 --> 01:42:54.000
and work on solving a common problem.

01:42:55.000 --> 01:42:59.000
Ineffective communication is the type of communication

01:43:00.000 --> 01:43:03.000
that leads to an active, vigorous discussion,

01:43:04.000 --> 01:43:07.000
but does not promote your group to solve a business problem.

01:43:08.000 --> 01:43:11.000
The conditions of effective communication.

01:43:12.000 --> 01:43:14.000
In order for your meeting to be effective,

01:43:15.000 --> 01:43:19.000
it is important that the communication between you and your subordinates

01:43:20.000 --> 01:43:25.000
comes from certain roles, from the understanding that the meeting is a job,

01:43:26.000 --> 01:43:28.000
and at work we all play a certain role.

01:43:29.000 --> 01:43:32.000
The role is a requirement for behavior.

01:43:32.000 --> 01:43:36.000
Below we will talk about the roles of the meeting,

01:43:37.000 --> 01:43:41.000
what roles the leader plays, what roles other participants of the meeting play.

01:43:42.000 --> 01:43:46.000
Expressive or interrupted communication

01:43:47.000 --> 01:43:51.000
is based on emotions, on the emotional reactions of the participants of the meeting.

01:43:52.000 --> 01:43:54.000
Something can capture you very much.

01:43:55.000 --> 01:43:59.000
Either you or any of the participants of the meeting

01:43:59.000 --> 01:44:04.000
want to achieve their own destructive goals.

01:44:05.000 --> 01:44:09.000
They want to achieve their own goals that are destructive.

01:44:10.000 --> 01:44:14.000
This type of communication is characterized by assessments,

01:44:15.000 --> 01:44:20.000
assessments of the correctness or incorrectness of the statements of other participants of the meeting.

01:44:21.000 --> 01:44:25.000
It is characterized by criticism, personalization and, perhaps, insults.

01:44:26.000 --> 01:44:30.000
You, as a leader, should make sure that your subordinates

01:44:31.000 --> 01:44:34.000
do not switch to an expressive type of communication.

01:44:35.000 --> 01:44:37.000
The roles of the participants of the meeting.

01:44:38.000 --> 01:44:42.000
Moderator, secretary, reporter and leader.

01:44:43.000 --> 01:44:47.000
The moderator monitors the compliance of the agenda.

01:44:48.000 --> 01:44:51.000
The secretary helps the reporter.

01:44:51.000 --> 01:44:56.000
The reporter organizes the entire process of the meeting.

01:44:57.000 --> 01:45:00.000
The reporter provides some information.

01:45:01.000 --> 01:45:10.000
The leader manages the meeting and makes the final decision on any issue.

01:45:11.000 --> 01:45:13.000
The result of the meeting.

01:45:14.000 --> 01:45:17.000
The first is the opinion of the participants of the meeting.

01:45:18.000 --> 01:45:20.000
Opinions can be different.

01:45:21.000 --> 01:45:23.000
The first is the opinion of the participants of the meeting.

01:45:24.000 --> 01:45:26.000
Remember how often you have a thought in your head.

01:45:27.000 --> 01:45:29.000
Again, I wasted my time in vain.

01:45:30.000 --> 01:45:34.000
Yes, perhaps, you should listen to the words of Ivan Petrovich.

01:45:35.000 --> 01:45:36.000
This is an opinion.

01:45:37.000 --> 01:45:40.000
The second result is the action.

01:45:41.000 --> 01:45:45.000
After the meeting, you went to perform some task.

01:45:46.000 --> 01:45:48.000
Or your subordinates went to perform some task.

01:45:48.000 --> 01:45:49.000
The third result is the action.

01:45:50.000 --> 01:45:51.000
The document.

01:45:52.000 --> 01:45:56.000
The document is the necessary result of the meeting.

01:45:57.000 --> 01:46:01.000
Decision, order, report, something else.

01:46:02.000 --> 01:46:04.000
And the managerial decision.

01:46:05.000 --> 01:46:08.000
That is, the decision that you make as a leader.

01:46:09.000 --> 01:46:13.000
At the end of each meeting there are four results.

01:46:14.000 --> 01:46:15.000
They are in front of you.

01:46:15.000 --> 01:46:17.000
Conditions of effectiveness of the meeting.

01:46:18.000 --> 01:46:22.000
These are some principles that each participant of the meeting should be familiar with.

01:46:23.000 --> 01:46:26.000
It is best to do this directly before the start of the process.

01:46:27.000 --> 01:46:29.000
The first. The meeting is a job.

01:46:30.000 --> 01:46:35.000
This means that each participant of the meeting should be active.

01:46:36.000 --> 01:46:38.000
The meeting is not a place to rest.

01:46:39.000 --> 01:46:41.000
The meeting is one of the forms of work.

01:46:42.000 --> 01:46:44.000
Everyone gets paid for it.

01:46:45.000 --> 01:46:47.000
This means that no one will be able to sit aside.

01:46:48.000 --> 01:46:52.000
In the decision of the issue, each participant of the meeting should take part.

01:46:53.000 --> 01:46:56.000
The second. The meeting has a goal.

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:07.000
This principle means that the proposals of each member of the team should promote the team to achieve the goal.

01:47:08.000 --> 01:47:15.000
Following this principle will help you get rid of destructive goals that are not important for your team.

01:47:16.000 --> 01:47:18.000
The third. The meeting is not a sport.

01:47:19.000 --> 01:47:21.000
There is no place for personal ambitions.

01:47:22.000 --> 01:47:24.000
There is no place for personal transition.

01:47:25.000 --> 01:47:26.000
There are no right and wrong.

01:47:27.000 --> 01:47:30.000
There is an opinion and the effectiveness of these opinions.

01:47:31.000 --> 01:47:33.000
There are tasks and decisions.

01:47:34.000 --> 01:47:36.000
And the effectiveness of these decisions for your team.

01:47:37.000 --> 01:47:41.000
The fourth. The meeting is not a dispute.

01:47:42.000 --> 01:47:50.000
If you criticize, if a participant of the meeting criticizes some of the proposed solutions, he must propose his own alternative.

01:47:51.000 --> 01:47:54.000
If you criticize something, then propose your own solution.

01:47:55.000 --> 01:47:56.000
You can not criticize in general.

01:47:57.000 --> 01:47:58.000
The meeting is not a dispute.

01:47:59.000 --> 01:48:06.000
If the participants of the meeting follow these principles, you will always be able to achieve the result you think is necessary.

01:48:07.000 --> 01:48:14.000
So. Now we know that there is a certain structure, which allows effective meetings.

01:48:15.000 --> 01:48:18.000
What is the process of holding a meeting?

01:48:19.000 --> 01:48:21.000
The process can be divided into 7 stages.

01:48:22.000 --> 01:48:24.000
You can see them now on the screen.

01:48:25.000 --> 01:48:27.000
The first stage. Preparation stage.

01:48:28.000 --> 01:48:29.000
What tasks are solved at the preparation stage?

01:48:30.000 --> 01:48:34.000
First, determining the place and time of the meeting.

01:48:34.000 --> 01:48:38.000
Second, determining the composition of the participants of the meeting.

01:48:39.000 --> 01:48:44.000
Who of your employees is needed for the solution of any task?

01:48:45.000 --> 01:48:47.000
Third, determining the agenda.

01:48:48.000 --> 01:48:50.000
What tasks are relevant to you now?

01:48:51.000 --> 01:48:52.000
As a manager.

01:48:53.000 --> 01:48:54.000
What tasks are relevant to your company now?

01:48:55.000 --> 01:48:59.000
What tasks are relevant to your subordinates now?

01:49:00.000 --> 01:49:07.000
Next. Determining your personal relationship as a manager to the subject of the meeting.

01:49:08.000 --> 01:49:11.000
What do you want to achieve with the help of the meeting?

01:49:12.000 --> 01:49:14.000
What is the goal personally in front of you?

01:49:15.000 --> 01:49:23.000
If you do not answer this question before the meeting, there is a possibility that at the meeting you will face something unexpected.

01:49:24.000 --> 01:49:31.000
Therefore, before holding a meeting, it is important to understand what you personally want from this process.

01:49:32.000 --> 01:49:41.000
And the last task that is solved at the preparation stage is to inform the participants of the meeting that the meeting is taking place.

01:49:42.000 --> 01:49:47.000
Information about the place, time and agenda.

01:49:48.000 --> 01:49:50.000
Next stage.

01:49:50.000 --> 01:49:52.000
The stage of establishing contact.

01:49:53.000 --> 01:49:55.000
There are two components here.

01:49:56.000 --> 01:49:57.000
The formal and informal part.

01:49:58.000 --> 01:49:59.000
The informal part.

01:50:00.000 --> 01:50:01.000
What is the purpose of establishing contact?

01:50:02.000 --> 01:50:04.000
What is happening at this stage?

01:50:05.000 --> 01:50:06.000
Participants of the meeting meet.

01:50:07.000 --> 01:50:11.000
Often they work in different departments and do not often see each other.

01:50:12.000 --> 01:50:20.000
This is an opportunity to talk, exchange news, shake hands, smile, just look.

01:50:21.000 --> 01:50:24.000
This part is from 1 to 3 minutes.

01:50:25.000 --> 01:50:30.000
Usually it ends while all the participants of the meeting are in one room.

01:50:31.000 --> 01:50:32.000
And the formal part.

01:50:33.000 --> 01:50:35.000
Here you can highlight the following.

01:50:36.000 --> 01:50:38.000
Greetings, which is pronounced by the head of the meeting.

01:50:38.000 --> 01:50:39.000
The meeting's host.

01:50:40.000 --> 01:50:41.000
Agreement of the regulations.

01:50:42.000 --> 01:50:45.000
And the designation of roles.

01:50:46.000 --> 01:50:47.000
How does it happen?

01:50:49.000 --> 01:50:54.000
Today, Ivan Petrovich will tell us about the results of his work.

01:50:55.000 --> 01:51:00.000
After that, we will listen to the report of Ivan Ivanovich on the state of affairs at the production site.

01:51:01.000 --> 01:51:02.000
What is this for?

01:51:02.000 --> 01:51:09.000
This stage is necessary for your group to meet and start working.

01:51:10.000 --> 01:51:15.000
When you start your car, the starter works first, which starts the engine.

01:51:16.000 --> 01:51:20.000
The stage of establishing contact is the starter of your meeting.

01:51:21.000 --> 01:51:24.000
The next stage is the manifestation of the situation.

01:51:25.000 --> 01:51:26.000
What is it?

01:51:27.000 --> 01:51:28.000
This is the answer to a simple question.

01:51:29.000 --> 01:51:30.000
What are we going to talk about?

01:51:31.000 --> 01:51:33.000
There are three stages.

01:51:34.000 --> 01:51:37.000
The first is the definition of the subject of discussion.

01:51:38.000 --> 01:51:41.000
We often call the same things by different names.

01:51:42.000 --> 01:51:43.000
And vice versa.

01:51:44.000 --> 01:51:46.000
We can call the same names different things.

01:51:47.000 --> 01:51:50.000
It is very important to develop a general system of concepts.

01:51:51.000 --> 01:51:53.000
What are we talking about now?

01:51:54.000 --> 01:51:56.000
Definition of the subject of discussion.

01:51:56.000 --> 01:52:02.000
This can happen in a discussion or through acquaintance.

01:52:03.000 --> 01:52:06.000
You, as a leader, tell that we are now talking about...

01:52:07.000 --> 01:52:13.000
You name the topic and explain what you mean by this word.

01:52:15.000 --> 01:52:21.000
It is important to expand the definition of the problem that you are declaring.

01:52:22.000 --> 01:52:28.000
The next stage is the definition of the attitude of each participant of your meeting.

01:52:35.000 --> 01:52:36.000
Why each?

01:52:37.000 --> 01:52:40.000
First, you can get information that you did not think about before.

01:52:41.000 --> 01:52:44.000
Second, if at this stage one of the participants of the meeting is silent,

01:52:45.000 --> 01:52:47.000
does not express his attitude to the subject of discussion,

01:52:47.000 --> 01:52:52.000
it means that in the future he may not work on solving the problem,

01:52:53.000 --> 01:52:58.000
or return to this stage, stopping the work of the whole group.

01:52:59.000 --> 01:53:01.000
Saying, you know, and I think differently.

01:53:02.000 --> 01:53:04.000
You know, and it is not worth attention at all.

01:53:05.000 --> 01:53:09.000
Therefore, it is very important to understand how your working group relates to the task of the meeting.

01:53:10.000 --> 01:53:13.000
Is this topic relevant to them or not?

01:53:14.000 --> 01:53:18.000
And the last factor is the moderation of the process to the leaders.

01:53:19.000 --> 01:53:24.000
You, as a leader, are responsible for clearly determining the subject of the meeting

01:53:25.000 --> 01:53:31.000
and understand how relevant this task is for the participants.

01:53:32.000 --> 01:53:34.000
After you establish contact with your group,

01:53:35.000 --> 01:53:37.000
after the group established contact with each other,

01:53:38.000 --> 01:53:40.000
with you, as the leader of the meeting,

01:53:40.000 --> 01:53:43.000
the stage of choosing priorities comes.

01:53:44.000 --> 01:53:45.000
What is it?

01:53:46.000 --> 01:53:48.000
The answer to the question, what is more important to us,

01:53:49.000 --> 01:53:51.000
which of the items in the meeting is more important to us.

01:53:52.000 --> 01:53:54.000
This happens in two ways.

01:53:55.000 --> 01:53:56.000
The first is by voting.

01:53:57.000 --> 01:54:02.000
We vote which task is more important to us as a team at the moment,

01:54:03.000 --> 01:54:05.000
or by the will of the leader.

01:54:06.000 --> 01:54:09.000
You decide as a leader what is more important to the team now.

01:54:10.000 --> 01:54:13.000
We will work with you on the solution of the task.

01:54:14.000 --> 01:54:20.000
It is important to speak out the points of view of each participant when choosing a priority.

01:54:21.000 --> 01:54:24.000
Firstly, this gives the opportunity to each participant to be heard.

01:54:25.000 --> 01:54:28.000
And secondly, it gives the opportunity to the leader,

01:54:29.000 --> 01:54:31.000
speaking out the point of view,

01:54:32.000 --> 01:54:35.000
to understand more about the problem that is relevant to him.

01:54:35.000 --> 01:54:40.000
So, the culmination of the meeting is the stage of transferring problems into tasks.

01:54:41.000 --> 01:54:46.000
You have gathered at this meeting to solve some problem,

01:54:47.000 --> 01:54:49.000
to increase the efficiency of your activity.

01:54:50.000 --> 01:54:52.000
What should be done for this?

01:54:53.000 --> 01:54:55.000
For this problem, which has no solution,

01:54:56.000 --> 01:54:58.000
you need to transfer it into a task,

01:54:59.000 --> 01:55:01.000
which your team can solve.

01:55:02.000 --> 01:55:03.000
For this you need to go through three stages.

01:55:03.000 --> 01:55:05.000
The first one is to answer the question,

01:55:06.000 --> 01:55:08.000
what is preventing us as a team,

01:55:09.000 --> 01:55:11.000
what is preventing our company from being effective?

01:55:12.000 --> 01:55:16.000
The second one is to understand what we want to be.

01:55:17.000 --> 01:55:19.000
What is the ideal situation?

01:55:20.000 --> 01:55:22.000
What should be the ideal situation?

01:55:23.000 --> 01:55:25.000
What should our company be like?

01:55:26.000 --> 01:55:27.000
How should we function?

01:55:28.000 --> 01:55:30.000
And the third, the most important,

01:55:30.000 --> 01:55:33.000
what should we do to be like this?

01:55:34.000 --> 01:55:35.000
When you find the answer to the question,

01:55:36.000 --> 01:55:37.000
what should we do,

01:55:38.000 --> 01:55:40.000
your problem, which, as I said, has no solution,

01:55:41.000 --> 01:55:42.000
is transferred into a task,

01:55:43.000 --> 01:55:45.000
which your team is able to solve.

01:55:46.000 --> 01:55:48.000
How to find the answer to these questions?

01:55:49.000 --> 01:55:50.000
Very simple.

01:55:51.000 --> 01:55:52.000
With the help of brainstorming.

01:55:53.000 --> 01:55:55.000
The result of this stage is the product of the meeting.

01:55:56.000 --> 01:55:58.000
It is an order that describes the actions

01:55:58.000 --> 01:56:00.000
that your employees should take

01:56:01.000 --> 01:56:03.000
to solve a given task.

01:56:04.000 --> 01:56:06.000
So, your meeting is already in full swing.

01:56:07.000 --> 01:56:10.000
You have identified a relevant problem for your team.

01:56:11.000 --> 01:56:15.000
Moreover, you were even able to transfer this problem

01:56:16.000 --> 01:56:18.000
to the task that requires a solution.

01:56:19.000 --> 01:56:23.000
How to understand that your meeting is going in the path of efficiency?

01:56:24.000 --> 01:56:26.000
To do this, look at what is happening.

01:56:26.000 --> 01:56:28.000
There are some signs.

01:56:29.000 --> 01:56:31.000
When is the meeting effective?

01:56:32.000 --> 01:56:34.000
The meeting is effective if there is a discussion,

01:56:35.000 --> 01:56:38.000
if your participants are involved in the process,

01:56:39.000 --> 01:56:41.000
if you discuss the agenda,

01:56:42.000 --> 01:56:45.000
the questions that were put on the agenda.

01:56:46.000 --> 01:56:51.000
The meeting is effective if the possibilities of solving the task are discussed.

01:56:51.000 --> 01:56:53.000
Your participants say,

01:56:54.000 --> 01:56:56.000
let's do it.

01:56:57.000 --> 01:57:00.000
They propose all kinds of solutions.

01:57:01.000 --> 01:57:05.000
The meeting is effective if specific proposals are made.

01:57:06.000 --> 01:57:08.000
One of the participants says,

01:57:09.000 --> 01:57:11.000
I propose and describe the actions.

01:57:12.000 --> 01:57:14.000
I would like to propose,

01:57:15.000 --> 01:57:18.000
and this phrase follows the description of a specific action.

01:57:18.000 --> 01:57:21.000
Your meeting is already effective

01:57:22.000 --> 01:57:24.000
if after 40 minutes after the meeting,

01:57:25.000 --> 01:57:27.000
you were able to make at least one decision.

01:57:28.000 --> 01:57:30.000
Any decision.

01:57:31.000 --> 01:57:33.000
For example, we finish in 20 minutes.

01:57:34.000 --> 01:57:36.000
The meeting lasts only an hour.

01:57:37.000 --> 01:57:39.000
If you were able to make at least one decision,

01:57:40.000 --> 01:57:42.000
it means that your team can work.

01:57:43.000 --> 01:57:46.000
The meeting is ineffective if you observe the following situation.

01:57:47.000 --> 01:57:49.000
If one of your participants

01:57:50.000 --> 01:57:53.000
allows himself to evaluate the personality of other participants.

01:57:54.000 --> 01:57:56.000
Mary Ivanovna, you said nonsense.

01:57:57.000 --> 01:58:02.000
Ivan Petrovich, you don't understand anything in the question you are talking about.

01:58:03.000 --> 01:58:07.000
If one of your participants allows himself to evaluate the personality of others,

01:58:08.000 --> 01:58:11.000
it means that the meeting is not effective.

01:58:11.000 --> 01:58:13.000
If your meeting is ineffective,

01:58:14.000 --> 01:58:16.000
if you can observe a lot of negativity.

01:58:17.000 --> 01:58:19.000
No, it's impossible.

01:58:20.000 --> 01:58:22.000
No, it won't work.

01:58:23.000 --> 01:58:25.000
No, this task is unsolvable.

01:58:26.000 --> 01:58:28.000
If you hear the word no,

01:58:29.000 --> 01:58:31.000
you as a leader need to think what is happening.

01:58:32.000 --> 01:58:34.000
Perhaps you have not yet identified the problem.

01:58:35.000 --> 01:58:37.000
Perhaps your team is fighting to solve the problem.

01:58:37.000 --> 01:58:39.000
Your meeting will not be effective

01:58:40.000 --> 01:58:43.000
if your subordinates or you use a subjunctive.

01:58:44.000 --> 01:58:47.000
It would be possible if you describe any situation.

01:58:48.000 --> 01:58:50.000
Yes, of course, everything can be solved

01:58:51.000 --> 01:58:53.000
only if you describe any situation.

01:58:54.000 --> 01:58:56.000
If you use a subjunctive.

01:58:57.000 --> 01:58:59.000
If you use a subjunctive,

01:59:00.000 --> 01:59:02.000
it is possible that the meeting will not be effective.

01:59:03.000 --> 01:59:05.000
If you use a subjunctive,

01:59:05.000 --> 01:59:07.000
it is possible that you will not solve the problem.

01:59:08.000 --> 01:59:10.000
If you hear that you often use a subjunctive,

01:59:11.000 --> 01:59:13.000
take a closer look.

01:59:14.000 --> 01:59:16.000
Perhaps you are solving not a task, but a problem.

01:59:17.000 --> 01:59:19.000
You should also be warned

01:59:20.000 --> 01:59:23.000
if you hear that you often use a subjunctive.

01:59:24.000 --> 01:59:27.000
Some of your participants most likely disagree

01:59:28.000 --> 01:59:32.000
with the agenda or the general view of the team on the situation.

01:59:32.000 --> 01:59:34.000
Then you need to return to the second point,

